doc.after: The Singaporean military is arguably the most technologically advanced in Southeast Asia.[128] It comprises the Singapore Army, Republic of Singapore Navy, and Republic of Singapore Air Force. It is seen as the guarantor of the country's independence.[129] The nation's philosophy of defence is one of diplomacy and deterrence.[130] This principle translates into the culture, involving all citizens in the country's defence.[131] The government spends 4.9% of the country's GDP on the military, and one out of every four dollars of government spending is spent on defence.[132]
